    "summary": "The user asks the assistant for a summary of the US Civil Rights Movement and subsequently probes whether the mainstream historical narrative is biased toward moderate leaders at the expense of more radical groups like the Black Panthers. The assistant responds by acknowledging the complexity of the movement, validating that school curricula often favor moderate narratives while noting that historians view both moderate and radical strategies as significant.",
